Title: Philodendron El Choco Red
Body (HTML):
Philodendron el choco red is a climbing Aroid with velvety leaves. The leaves start out with a striking red abaxial leaf surface that is somewhat fading once the leaves mature.

 

CARE:

Medium to high humidity. It will usually tolerate indoor levels with slight difficulty and will appreciate additional humidity if available. Grows best in 65-80 degrees F and will tolerate as low as 50 degrees for a short period of time. Cold-sensitive and will show it when upset.

Light:
Bright indirect light indoors (north or east-facing windows). Do not leave in direct, all-day sun. Grow in full to partial shade outdoors.

Soil:
Superior aroid mix or superior-draining peat based mix. Some chunky material is required to provide necessary and constant airflow to the roots.

Water:
This plant is slightly water loving in its native habitat, but indoors should dry out slightly between watering. Soggy or overly damp soil may encourage leaf drop and disease. Decrease water in winter.

Fertilizer:
For proper growth, use a balanced fertilizer ever 1-2 months during the growing period.
Tags: Medium Light High, New arrivals, rare plants, Tropical plant

Title: Philodendron Gloriosum
Body (HTML):
It is within the Philodendron genus and is a crawling Philodendron with heartleaf-shaped green velvety foliage and pale to striking white veins. 

By crawling we mean creeping on the ground. Its stem grows horizontally along the surface. Philodendrons are either climbers or creepers. This one is a creeper.

The plant is native to Colombia and other tropical parts of the world. Apart from Colombia, it is found in Mexico, Central America as well as Peru, Ecuador, the western parts of Brazil and Venezuela.

 Soil: Aroid mix

High humidity

Title: Fatsia japonica
Body (HTML):

Title: Pellionia repens
Body (HTML):

Title: Lipstick Plant
Body (HTML):
Aeschynanthus japhrolepis aka lipstick plant is a vigorous growth, easy care trailing plant that will be adorned with red blooms as long as the ideal growing conditions are met.

This stunning plant originates from the Brazilian rainforests, which is exactly why it loves high humidity. Weekly misting or a well placed humidifier will help it flourish and reach its full potential of being around 1.2 meters in length.

Light: Bright indirect

Water: allow the top 1-2 inches of the pot to dry between waterings

Size: 4" nursery pot

Title: Tradescantia palida
Body (HTML):

Give this plant a spot with bright indirect light and it will reward you with fast growing beautifully coloured foliage and small lilac flowers.

Light: Bright indirect

Water: Water thoroughly and allow the top inch of soil to dry between waterings.

Size: 4" nursery pot

Title: Olive Tree
Body (HTML):
Bring a piece of the Mediterranean into your home with this beautiful little olive tree. It's sage green foliage works so well in a bright and airy modern space. 

Eventually growing to around 10 feet in height this little plant can become the star of your sunny window display and can be left to grow in a bushy form or pruned to become a standard, maybe you could even try your hand at some topiary.

It comes as no surprise that olives love full sun and require around 66 hours of direct sunlight per day to thrive.

Combine with a terracotta planter to achieve that Tuscan vibe we all love.

Botanical Name: Olea europaea

Light: Full sun for 6 hours per day

Water: Allow the top inch of soil to dry before watering. Thrives in cactus mix soil.

Size: 4" nursery pot or 6"
Tags: Easy care, High Light

Title: Alocasia scalprum
Body (HTML):
Alocasia scalprum is a truly stunning plant that is native only to the Philippines. This beautiful rare plant has sword shaped foliage that starts out bright green and waxy, then slowly transforms to a dark blue/green color with deep veining throughout the leaf.

Light requirements: Grows best with bright indirect light but can happily tolerate lower light conditions.

Water & Soil: Pot into a free draining soil blend that is suited to aroids, water frequently but with small amounts making sure that the soil is never waterlogged.

Size: 4" pot
Standardized Product Type: Home & Garden > Plants > Indoor & Outdoor Plants > Potted Houseplants
Tags: Medium Light High, Medium Light Low, rare plants, Tropical plant

Title: Calathea White Fusion
Body (HTML):
Calathea white fusion is one of our team favourites, the white variegation with pink hues sets this little calathea apart from the rest of its family. Native to parts of Mexico and South America, this beautiful plant brings a truly special tropical vibe to any home.

Light requirements: To maintain the distinctive variegation, it loves bright filtered or indirect light. Direct sunlight will cause sun scorch on the white sections of the foliage.

Water & Soil : Keep this little plant consistently moist, but never wet or waterlogged. For best results a light and airy soil with good drainage and moisture retention.

Size: 4" pot
Standardized Product Type: Home & Garden > Plants

Title: Alocasia Dragon Scale
Body (HTML):
Alocasia Dragon Scale is one of the most distinctive members of the Alocasia family, with its striking dark and silver deeply veined foliage it instantly draws your attention. These beautiful plants are a cultivated variety of Alocasia baginda, a native to the jungles of Borneo.

Light requirements: For optimal growth place your Alocasia dragons scale in a spot with bright indirect light, avoid direct sun to prevent leaf scorch.

Water & Soil : This plant loves a chunky aroid soil mixture containing coir, perlite and orchid bark. Soak the growing medium fully when watering and allow the pot to dry out half way down before watering again.

Size: 4 inch pot
Tags: Medium Light High, Medium Light Low, rare plants, Tropical plant

Title: Moisture Meter  by Classy Casita
Body (HTML):
Keep your watering skills on point 

Ideal soil test tool kit for house plants, garden, lawn and farm.

ACCURATE: This moisture meter measures the level of wetness between 1 - 10. Level 1 means very dry, and level 10 means very wet.

No plants can tolerate the two extremes for long, so it is important to often check on all of your plants.

NOTE: Do not use to test very dry soil. Do not use to test water or other liquid. Designed to only test soil.

Title: Meliora Soy Candle
Body (HTML):
Soy Wax and Essential oils
9 oz. Wooden wick. 45-60 hours of burn time.


Dewy Meadow: Lime, white ginger, lily, and balsam


Dark & Stormy: With heart notes of musky cashmere, silky suede, and bold sandalwood and frankincense, this scent is the perfect pair with a rainy or gloomy day. 


Candle Safety: 

To avoid fire hazard, never leave a burning candle unattended and always light on a heat proof surface. Keep out of reach of flammable objects, pets, children, or anything that may catch on fire. Do not burn the candle for more than 4 hours at a time. Stop use when only 1/2” of wax remains. 

Cleaning Your Candle Jar or Vintage Vessel:

When candle has 1/2" left of wax, fill jar with boiling water and leave over night or for 6+ hours to allow wax to cool. Once wax is cooled, pick out with your hands and dispose of in the garbage or green bin - DO NOT POUR IN THE SINK. Once wax is removed from the jar, wash normally and voila!

Title: Mounted Staghorn Fern Workshop
Body (HTML):
I'm so excited to introduce our new Workshop 👉
.

"Join us for a masterclass on preparing, mounting & maintaining your very own staghorn fern (platycerium bifurcatum)

The workshop runs for around 1.5 hours and is as hands on as it gets, you'll walk away with a fully completed mounted staghorn, ready to hang on the wall in your home.

These incredible plants really are one of the true gems in the world of horticulture. We will breifly dive into talking about how they live in nature and how you can mimic that environment within your home. We will also talk about one of their most fascinating traits that has astounded the plant world since it's discovery... You'll just have to come along and find out what it is.

With wine, snacks and some great company it's sure to be a lot of fun.

Join us on the 23rd of April for this very special workshop.

6 pm to 7:30 pm
.
Workshop instructor: Joe Spiers .
.
Tags: gifts, workshop

Title: Philodendron Green Kokedama
Body (HTML):
Kokedamas are one of our featured one-of-a-kind items, they are great gift ideas or centerpieces.
It's a new, fun, and creative way to present plants.


Kokedama means Moss-ball, it's a Japanese technique where you wrap the root system of the plant in a ball of soil that is after covered with green or sphagnum moss.
They come in many varieties of plants and sizes.

Title: Calathea White Star

Calathea white Star is one of our team favourites, the white variegation with pink hues sets this little calathea apart from the rest of its family.

Native to parts of Mexico and South America, this beautiful plant brings a truly special tropical vibe to any home.

Light requirements: To maintain the distinctive variegation, it loves bright filtered or indirect light. Direct sunlight will cause sun scorch on the white sections of the foliage.

Water & Soil : Keep this little plant consistently moist, but never wet or waterlogged. For best results a light and airy soil with good drainage and moisture retention.

Title: Marphyl Soil Enhancer

• MARPHYL’s liquid soil enhancer can be used on plants, vegetables, flowers, lawns, trees, greenhouses, garden, indoor plants and hydroponics
  • 100% natural, organic, vegan, eco-friendly, Non-GMO product
  • Marine Phytoplankton are micro algae that is full of nutrients, vitamins and minerals
  • Naturally boosts plant health by replenishing the soil as plants grow and use the nutrients in the soil
  • Recommended use is once every 2 weeks in ratio of 1:20 with fresh water
Tags: fertilizer, fertilizer plant food

Title: Leca Pebbles
Body (HTML):
These clay pebbles are nothing but the tiny clay balls undergone high-temperature heat. When fired in a kiln these tiny pebbles expand and become porous from within. Some people also call them Hydroponic Clay Balls, Hydroton, clay pebbles, or light expanded clay aggregate (LECA). 

hydrotons are great water absorbers, it collects the excess water and stores it for later use.  It prevents roots from being damaged due to excess water. Generally, clay pebbles are used as a base layer or alongside to help plants get the proper amount of water and air through it.

Title: Sphagnum Moss 150gr
Body (HTML):
Use Sphagnum moss for seed starting, as a planting medium for orchids, as a potting soil amendment, for lining baskets, or for other art projects. It has a neutral pH level and is great for retaining moisture in the soil, even when dried.

You'll often see Sphagnum moss used for creating a Kokedama (which is a moss ball planter),
Tags: growing medium
